masses.additional_notes: Benign breast lesions tend to have more regular shapes, such as oval or round, and parallel orientation. The margins of benign lesions are often circumscribed. Echo patterns in benign lesions can vary, including anechoic, hyperechoic, complex cystic and solid, isoechoic, or homogeneous features. Benign lesions may also lack significant posterior features.
